      "opening_notes": "Trompowsky Attack (A45): Standard responses to 2.Bg5 are 2...Ne4 (directly challenging the bishop), 2...e6, or 2...d5. Playing 2...Nc6 allows White to execute the Trompowsky plan immediately with 3.Bxf6. After 3.Bxf6, recapturing with gxf6 (rather than exf6) was a coherent positional choice \u2014 it opens the g-file and enables the Bg7 fianchetto, trading structural weakness for active piece play. The bishop pair advantage gained after White voluntarily traded both bishops for knights (Bxf6 and Bxc6+) was the foundation of the win."
